      "writtenOn": "2020-11-23T18:47:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t follow Gerrit notation here. CV needs a short name for \"revision number\".\nI use `patchset` to mean monotonically increasing number identifying it. Admittedly, this is old Rietveld notation, which probably originates from Critique predecessor.\nTo my best knowledge, this is also how most other ChOps code uses it, LUCI in particular (though I don\u0027t know about Tricium)",
